## Why this dual-license model?

Knowledge should be free and accessible to everyone. The CC BY-SA 4.0 license
on the content guarantees that anyone — individuals, institutions, or
businesses — can use, adapt, and even sell this material, as long as they
attribute the original author and keep the derived work under the same open
license. This way, if you encounter a paid version of this content somewhere,
you can always find a free version by tracing it back to its source.

The MIT license on the source code allows the technical implementation to be
reused freely without the ShareAlike obligation, which is standard practice
for open-source educational sites.

